Author: Tyler Van Hoomissen

Install

$ cd grunt
$ npm install

Installing selenium for local runs

$ cd grunt
$ grunt shell:install_selenium
$ grunt shell:start_selenium


Running against the selenium hub

$ cd grunt
$ grunt test:e2e:build --repo_name=saas-portal-tyler

Replace repo name with your own. This will run the tests against the selenium hub,
which runs against that repo on Hercules.


Running locally against selenium

$ cd grunt
$ grunt shell:start_selenium
Open new tab
$ cd grunt
$ grunt test:e2e


Development

Needed documentation to write tests:
- Intern: https://theintern.github.io/intern
- LeadFoot: https://theintern.github.io/leadfoot
- Chai Assert: http://chaijs.com/api/assert/
- Faker: http://marak.com/faker.js/
